Title: [ANN][PRE-SALE]🔑CRYDE🚘 A car raffle platform, with profit sharing💰
Body: Hello TimeTeller,  First of all, Sorry for the late reply!  And now some answers: Customs taxes are not included with the prize, however transport and shipping expenses will be covered.  There are 3 solutions as of now to get rid of import,customs taxes,  1, Plenty of luxury brands offer worldwide coverage. We can order a car through the manufacturers local advocacy (the nearest dealership to us) and get the order filled by Your local dealership. This way, it's not one bit more difficult for the winner, than walking into the local dealership and buying a car from them.  2, The winner can always choose ETH payout instead of the car, which equals to the 80% of the car's MSRP paid to the winner in ETH.  3, We are currently consulting with dealerships directly on the main continents, and bigger countries, to provide an even smoother customer service, eliminating the need of 2 dealerships (as in solution 1).  Should you have other questions, don't hesitate to ask us!

Author: CRYDE.IO
Title: [ANN][PRE-SALE]🔑CRYDE🚘 A car raffle platform, with profit sharing💰
Body: Hello MelodyCrypto,  CRYDE and Cryder have no common points in the concept (except using the blockchain), you just have to read the first sentence in both ANN-s or websites. We have no contact with Cryder, this is a brand new project by a totally different team.  Cryder is a ride sharing platform, similar to UBER and a lot of ride sharing blockchain projects as we see, while CRYDE is a unique raffle platform, where participants can win cars, or ETH.  Should you have any other questions, we are here to help!

Title: [ANN][PRE-SALE]🔑CRYDE🚘 A car raffle platform, with profit sharing💰
Body: Don't think there have been too many raffle crypto projects so the project is definitely interesting in that regard, however one could be skeptical of the long term economic viability of the project for the team as well as investors. If the weekly raffle is intended to be a dream car then the initial 70% of ICO funds allotted for weekly prizes should deplete very fast, then it seems the rest of the money needed for the weekly prizes would depend on the price of the CRYDE tokens the team can obtain by selling the raffled tokens on exchanges, which would be subject to massive weekly sell pressure they themselves are creating to obtain the weekly prize money in the potentially vicious cycle.

Quote from: Andeze17 on April 29, 2018, 01:03:30 PM Don't think there have been too many raffle crypto projects so the project is definitely interesting in that regard, however one could be skeptical of the long term economic viability of the project for the team as well as investors. If the weekly raffle is intended to be a dream car then the initial 70% of ICO funds allotted for weekly prizes should deplete very fast, then it seems the rest of the money needed for the weekly prizes would depend on the price of the CRYDE tokens the team can obtain by selling the raffled tokens on exchanges, which would be subject to massive weekly sell pressure they themselves are creating to obtain the weekly prize money in the potentially vicious cycle.  Hello Andeze17,  I'm not sure that our description of the project is really clear right now (working on it at the moment, new content should be up anytime now).  70% of the ICO funds(Main-sale funds) should last for at least 45-55 weeks after launch. Raffle tickets can be primarily bought by ETH, BTC, LTC (more to come), the ability to buy raffle tickets at $2/token rate with your CRD is just an extra function of the CRD tokens to keep them circulating. The income from selling (used) CRD tokens on exchanges is NOT our main income source.  We don't believe that we might create a vicious cycle, rather the opposite. As an investor, you could: Buy CRD tokens right now at $0.173 and lock them in our dividend smart contract for stable monthly income; sell them upon launch for a ROI of nearly 1200%; or use them to buy raffle tickets at a price of $2/token securing a 91% discount. As a player, you could: Buy CRD tokens right now at $0.173 and use your tokens to buy raffle tickets at a price of $2/token securing a 91% discount.  Since every used CRD token will be put up for sale at an asking price of minimum $2/CRD; the fact that CRD Tokens can be used to get profit dividend and the opportunity to buy tickets at a fixed $2/token presumably creates an artifical floor on exchanges for CRD Tokens near $2/token.  Should you have any questions regarding CRYDE, feel free to ask us on Telegram @AaronCRYDE , @GeorgeCRYDE , @CRYDEofficial or send us a message on LinkedIn, e-mail (can be found on https://cryde.io).

Title: [ANN][PRE-SALE]🔑CRYDE🚘 A car raffle platform, with profit sharing💰
Body: Hello Iphifenia!  If you're interested in our project, you can follow us on twitter @crydeio or join us on telegram at https://t.me/crydeio.  Quote from: antiqklasik on April 22, 2018, 01:13:52 PM your project is very interesting and unique, get the dream car is not impossible. what are the other advantages of the CRYDE project, because there are many competitors in the ICO market  Hey antiqklasik!  We've looked everywhere for a raffle platform like CRYDE, but none of them suited our needs. That's why we're creating CRYDE. A dream car raffle platform(for now) with profit dividends. It's the perfect platform for both investors and users. The main advantages of CRYDE are:     •During our ICO, tokens can be bought for $0.173-$0.26. After our platform launches, each token can be used to buy raffle tickets at a flat rate of $2/token     •You can lock your CRD tokens in our dividend smart contract, which grants you monthly profit dividends paid in ETH (At 0.8% of online gamblig market share obtained, 1ETH of investment would earn you 0.7ETH/week after our launch.)     •Investors can actively participate in the further development of CRYDE,you'll be able to vote on various things, like further raffle categories(luxury watches,smaller boats etc.) or more frequent draws(more than 1/week)     •Fully transparent operations, our investor's dashboard will show you anything from handling prize funds,drawing the winning tickets,weekly incomes and expenses of CRYDE, worth of your tokens, % of all tokens locked in the dividend contract, total dividends earned etc.   Quote from: tzuzulmbakzul on April 22, 2018, 01:21:07 PM very interesting project, what is the minimum token sales target?   Hi tzuzulmbakzul!  We don't have a minimum token sales target, we are starting the development either way. However, sales of tokens would be a huge help to us, we could expand our team providing a faster launch of the CRYDE platform, it would cover legal and marketing expenses and secure the prizes for the first few raffles for example the Mustang raffle at $300k raised and the Porsche 718 at $1m raised at the end of our pre-sale, showing people what CRYDE's really about.
